				<td colspan="2"><span>Basics: I have a Pentium II ~400 MZ, Windows 2000. 384 KB ram, which is max possible for my system (3 slots able to hold max 128 each). GeForce 4 MX420 Vid card (64 Megs) and average speed cable internet.
<br />

<br />
Problem: I can't seem to AE or chant kite. Every time a song goes into effect (directly after the spell timer bar hits max) I get a little twitch, during which I stop moving for a split second, and everything else keeps moving. On my end it looks as if the mobs warp slightly closer to me. If I stay far enough away that the mobs don't warp right next to me and hit me every 3 songs, I'm too far away to have my spells hit.
<br />

<br />
Solutions: First I simply tried less populated zones, hoping that would help, but no luck there. I have also turned my spell density all the way off, and dropped my clip plane to the closest possible, to no avail. I consider myself a pretty good group bard, but at my level (33) the xp is starting to drop from about 1 level per hour to 1 every three or so hours, and it's killing me to go so slowly. I see NO difference with EqPlaynice too. If anyone has suggestions, knows what the problem is, or at least can tell me that the twitches are normal, please speak up. 
<br />

<br />
-Selo
<br />

<br />
P.S. I know I need to get a new system, I just don't have the money, so buying new stuff is not an option for me at this point.</span></td>
